'''NFPA 1670''' (''Standard on Operations and Training for Technical Search and Rescue Incidents'') is a [[Technical standard|standard]] published by the [[National Fire Protection Association]].

== Purpose ==
This standard shall identify and establish levels of functional capability for conducting operations at technical [[search and rescue]] incidents while minimizing threats to rescuers.{{cite web | url=http://www.nfpa.org/aboutthecodes/AboutTheCodes.asp?DocNum=1670 | title=NFPA 1670 | accessdate=November 19, 2012}}

